19/03/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Deputy Prime Minister Goran Granic, Justice Minister Ingrid Anticevic Marinovic and the resident office of the European Commission in Zagreb presented a programme Tuesday (18 March) for reforming state administration.
Officials say the chief goal is to implement a modern system of public services and efficient institutional structures.
Also Tuesday, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro signed a set of agreements regulating pension and other social insurance rights.
The documents arrange to pay benefits to citizens who have made contributions in both countries.
The talks on insurance rights began in 1997.
(HINA, HRT - 18/03/03)
